South Korea Stock Movers: Poongsan, Samsung Securities, S-Oil

-- B y   S a e r o m i   S h i n
-- 
2011-08-09T02:19:33Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-09/south-korea-stock-movers-poongsan-samsung-securities-s-oil.html
Shares of the following companies had
unusual moves in South Korea trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 11:18 a.m. in  Seoul . The  Kospi
Index (KOSPI)  tumbled 9.4 percent to 1,693.94. The stock gauge has
fallen 24 percent from its May 2 high. A decline of 20 percent
or more signals a so-called  bear market  to some investors.  Brokerages: Samsung Securities Co. (016360 KS) tumbled 10
percent to 62,200 won, the steepest drop since Oct. 24, 2008.
Daewoo Securities Co. (006800 KS) lost 9.5 percent to 13,750
won. Hyundai Securities Co. (003450 KS) sank 9.4 percent to
9,420 won. Brokerages on concern a stock-market slump will curb
share trading as the Kospi slumped for a sixth day.  Refiners: SK Innovation Co. (096770 KS) lost 6.7 percent to
166,500 won.  GS Holdings (078930)  Corp. (078930 KS) sank 7.3 percent to
69,600 won.  S-Oil Corp. (010950)  (010950 KS) dropped 7.3 percent to
120,000 won. Oil futures in  New York  slumped to the lowest level
in since September.  Poongsan Corp. (103140 KS), a copper-products maker,
tumbled 10 percent to 36,500 won, as copper futures in New York
slumped for the seventh straight day. It was the stockâ€™s biggest
drop since Nov. 6, 2008.  To contact the reporter on this story:
